<font color="#FF0000">FOLLOW UP ON COOK AND FISHING</font><br>
<tt>Sat Sep 13 17:28:23 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Cook, others, man I am glad we have decided to fish on seperate sides of the lake (thread #111). I am exhausted after reading your post Cook.  You really are the master of jumping to wrong conclusions, and writing long posts, but be that as it may, you  are entitled to write em. I choose to read it, I was not forced. I have no guilt, no fear, and no remorse over my past, present, or future. My children know what I did &quot;in the war daddy&quot; and are proud of me. I still feel I am a true American and patriot. I never called a VietNam Vet a &quot;baby killer&quot; and despised the peacenik hynena pack mentality that did. Yes, I think most of my &quot;peace brothers&quot; sucked too. (surprised?)  Most of them were in the movement to save their own tails, and once they did, they were gone. Very few were there for deep held feelings and ideals about war and organized evil. Surprisingly, very few of them were actually commies too. Commie's were also considered as part of the establishment and war machine, and not to be trusted by the &quot;turn on and drop out&quot; group.<br><br>
As a licensed psychotherapist, I have spent almost 30 years working with and helping all kinds of people, and also, recognizing that there were those that I could not reach. The &quot;chemistry&quot; was wrong or they didn't want or need my input. A good shrinks knows when to NOT shrink, if you follow my logic.  Clearly that applies to us.  <br><br>
So now we fish on seperate sides of the lake, in peace I hope, and who knows, perhaps sometime in the future, one of us just might yell to the other: &quot;Hey they are biting over here, come on over.&quot; Perhaps not.  
